   <abstract lang="eng">To assess a national need for facilities to simulate atmospheric processes, a Colloquium on Atmospheric Simulation was set up to survey current laboratory experimentation on atmospheric processes over the course of a year. The bulk of the discussions in this Colloquium concentrate on the development of laboratory experimentation as a direct basic, scientific tool, rather than as a procedure for environmental simulation. Appendices are included in this report.</abstract>
